SIMPLE: crap
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Crap
<hw>Crap</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>In the
game of craps, a first throw of the dice in which the total is two,
three, or twelve, in which case the caster loses. Also called
<altname>craps</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>same as <er>excrement</er> and <er>feces</er>.</def>
<mark>[vulgar]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> shit.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>nonsense; balderdash; bullshit; -- also used as an
expletive.</def> <mark>[vulgar]</mark>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bullshit.</syn>
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crap</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Crap
<hw>Crap</hw> <pr>(kr⟦acr⟧p)</pr>, <pos>v.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>to
defecate. Same as <er>take a crap</er>.</def> <mark>[vulgar]</mark> ⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crapaud</ent>⟦br⟧
